            <p class="article-body">But what if this Gigantic Structure unknowingly leads on a  
                path, from where there is no turning around. How disastrous  
                it would be in case it collapses? In my wildest of the dreams, I  
                am incapable of even imaging how catastrophic results, it  
                can produce. 
                </p>
                
            <p class="article-body">The massive runoffs into the Yangtze river has led to worries  
                and doubts, concerning that the Three Gorges Dam would be  
                overstressed beyond its capacity to withstand the inflow.  
                These concerns were emerged from the frequent reports of  displacement, seepage, deformation, settlement in the substructure of dam. Although these threat  indicators are within normal parameters, still there remains a fear that the dam will collapse.
                    </p>
                    
            <p class="article-body">There are already some serious drawbacks of this colossal dam:</p>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p class="article-body">Migration: In order to construct such a huge dam many local homes, factories, farm lands had been  destroyed, causing people to leave their native land. Moreover, the money set aside for rehabilitation of such people was also pocketed by local government officials making things worse.
                            </p>
                </li>

                <li>
                    <p class="article-body">High Risk: Over 360 million people live within the water shed of Yangtze so if dam were to break by  any means may it be severe earthquake, heavy rainfall, millions of lives would be highly precarious. 
                            </p>
                </li>

                <li>
                    <p class="article-body">Increased Seismic Activity: There has been a rise in incidents of landslides destroying several homes in the valley because of the increasing added weight from the reservoir, large amount of pressure on the ground causing frequent earthquakes, which is severe threat to the dam’s strength.
                            </p>
                </li>

                <li>
                    <p class="article-body">Sewage Problem: 265 billion gallons of waste and sewage is dumped into Yangtze annually. As the  Dam has slowed down the pace of water flow, tremendous amounts of waste, sewage and toxic  materials accumulate in river adversely affecting marine life, thereby affecting the ecosystem. 

                            </p>
                </li>


            </ul>










